WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.000
You bought Dumbo?
How are we supposed to pay for this?

00:03.000 --> 00:04.000
US licence deal.

00:04.000 --> 00:05.640
I told you, there's no more rubber.

00:05.640 --> 00:06.840
I'll double the wholesale price.

00:06.840 --> 00:08.440
Where are you getting this money
from?

00:08.440 --> 00:09.920
I really need that dough, Newbie.

00:09.920 --> 00:10.920
We're on it.

00:10.920 --> 00:12.480
I already told you that, Trotter.

00:12.480 --> 00:13.560
Buddy!

00:13.560 --> 00:14.680
(LAUGHS) Mac!

00:14.680 --> 00:15.960
Shirley, this is Mac.

00:15.960 --> 00:18.120
Mac, the legendary S Kwong.

00:19.160 --> 00:20.160
China white.

00:22.200 --> 00:23.520
I wanna make you a partner.

00:23.520 --> 00:24.880
My name on the board?

00:24.880 --> 00:25.960
No.

00:25.960 --> 00:27.920
While you're in my shop,
they're Bare Feet boards.

00:27.920 --> 00:29.560
Hey, hey, hey. Hey.

00:29.560 --> 00:30.840
Argh!

00:30.840 --> 00:32.040
Get off!

00:33.320 --> 00:34.880
(SCREAMS) No!

00:36.440 --> 00:38.920
You ever wonder
if it could've worked between us,

00:38.920 --> 00:40.640
what it would've been like?

02:24.680 --> 02:26.240
(INAUDIBLE)

03:05.160 --> 03:06.880
(CAR DOOR SQUEAKS AND CLOSES)

03:15.480 --> 03:16.640
Trace?

03:16.640 --> 03:18.240
I locked it.

03:18.240 --> 03:19.440
Ah, what? Why?

03:19.440 --> 03:21.960
I saw you with Margaux, Trot,
so you know why.

03:24.840 --> 03:26.480
Ah, let me in, Trace.

03:27.480 --> 03:28.680
Please, Tracy.

03:33.000 --> 03:34.760
Tracy, please?

03:42.640 --> 03:44.760
Isn't this too big
to take into a bank?

03:44.760 --> 03:46.120
Hey?

03:46.120 --> 03:47.440
No, this one's just for show.

03:47.440 --> 03:49.120
We'll give out the real one
next year,

03:49.120 --> 03:52.800
when we actually hold the comp,
yeah?

03:52.800 --> 03:56.600
Yeah, but, Snap, what's gonna stop
someone just stealing this one

03:56.600 --> 03:58.680
and then cashing it in?

03:58.680 --> 04:00.560
It's like real money.

04:00.560 --> 04:02.600
Look at the date, Choc.

04:02.600 --> 04:04.480
It's for next year.

04:04.480 --> 04:06.040
Oh, yeah.

04:06.040 --> 04:08.280
Put it down. Put it down!

04:09.400 --> 04:12.120
Arthur Foreman.
Hey!

04:12.120 --> 04:14.960
Ah, mate, thank you so much
for coming all this way.

04:14.960 --> 04:16.400
Yeah, no.

04:16.400 --> 04:18.200
Brian,
it's great to finally meet you.

04:18.200 --> 04:20.720
Hey, ah, just call me Snapper,
mate. Everyone does.

04:20.720 --> 04:21.800
Snapper?
Uh-huh.

04:21.800 --> 04:23.560
Snapper. That's great.

04:23.560 --> 04:25.200
Who's this?
Yeah, I'm Choc.

04:25.200 --> 04:27.000
Choc. Snapper and Choc.
Hey.

04:27.000 --> 04:28.240
(LAUGHS)

04:28.240 --> 04:30.560
Uh-oh, I see you've already gone
to the liberty of, ah,

04:30.560 --> 04:31.720
of spending my money.

04:31.720 --> 04:34.160
No, I just wanted you to see
what it would look like, you know?

04:34.160 --> 04:35.200
Righto.

04:35.200 --> 04:36.920
We can always discuss the amount,
of course.

04:36.920 --> 04:39.040
No, it all looks, ah, tickety-boo.

04:39.040 --> 04:40.840
Been looking forward
to this weekend for months.

04:40.840 --> 04:41.840
Yeah.

04:41.840 --> 04:43.000
Shall we, ah...?

04:43.000 --> 04:44.760
Please.
Yeah.

04:44.760 --> 04:46.600
Come on, Brian. (LAUGHS)

04:47.960 --> 04:50.000
Yeah, I had a nickname at school.

04:50.000 --> 04:51.600
Foreskin?
Don't.

04:51.600 --> 04:52.720
No.

04:52.720 --> 04:54.720
No, no, they, ah...
they tried that one.

04:54.720 --> 04:56.760
No. No, I was, ah, the Dodger.

04:57.840 --> 04:59.200
Arthur.

04:59.200 --> 05:00.400
Arty.

05:01.400 --> 05:02.480
Artful.

05:03.560 --> 05:04.560
Dodger.

05:04.560 --> 05:06.360
You don't know Oliver Twist?

05:07.440 --> 05:08.440
Oh, ye...

05:08.440 --> 05:09.800
Oh, hey, so, ah, listen,

05:09.800 --> 05:11.960
I wanted to do this thing
with the competition next year.

05:11.960 --> 05:13.480
I wanted to do this thing
with the heats.

05:13.480 --> 05:17.080
I wanna call it 'Man on Man', hey?

05:17.080 --> 05:19.280
Well, no,
maybe we call it 'Foreman on Man'.

05:19.280 --> 05:22.160
(LAUGHS)
Right. Because...

05:22.160 --> 05:24.040
Right? (LAUGHS)

05:24.040 --> 05:25.200
Yeah. We'll think about it.

05:25.200 --> 05:27.640
Hey, do you think I could present
that big cheque of yours

05:27.640 --> 05:28.960
to the winner?

05:28.960 --> 05:30.680
Wait, so you're in?

05:30.680 --> 05:33.760
Mate, I wouldn't come all this way
if I wasn't gonna sponsor your comp.

05:33.760 --> 05:35.600
Great! (LAUGHS)

05:35.600 --> 05:37.920
Yeah, of course you can. Yeah.

05:37.920 --> 05:39.840
And you do all your manufacturing
here?

05:39.840 --> 05:41.040
Yeah. Yeah.

05:41.040 --> 05:43.360
We're, ah, actually about to start
a new line of boardshorts.

05:43.360 --> 05:45.520
I've been designing them myself.

05:45.520 --> 05:49.080
Give them that, ah,
Bare Feet vibe, you know?

05:49.080 --> 05:52.160
I hear there's a small issue
with your wetsuit rubber supplier,

05:52.160 --> 05:53.760
bit of competition
from down the road?

05:55.280 --> 05:57.000
You're well-informed.

05:57.000 --> 05:59.320
Never spend money unless
you've done your research, Snap.

06:00.360 --> 06:01.600
It's impressive.

06:01.600 --> 06:04.280
Yeah, well, we've been watching
you fellas for a while.

06:04.280 --> 06:06.400
LightWave have secured that US deal.

06:06.400 --> 06:08.280
Must make you a bit worried?

06:08.280 --> 06:09.320
No.

06:09.320 --> 06:11.680
Best way to lose control
of the, ah, product.

06:11.680 --> 06:13.240
Exactly.
Yeah.

06:13.240 --> 06:14.960
Yeah. Yeah.

06:14.960 --> 06:16.920
The original and the best,
am I right?

06:16.920 --> 06:18.080
Hey!

06:18.080 --> 06:21.280
Staying salty since 1969, ugh!

06:21.280 --> 06:22.800
(LAUGHS)

06:22.800 --> 06:24.800
I love that. I love that.

06:24.800 --> 06:26.040
(SIGHS CONTENTEDLY)

06:26.040 --> 06:28.400
You're buying this place?

06:28.400 --> 06:30.160
I'm thinking about it.

06:30.160 --> 06:31.800
What does Sharpie think?

06:31.800 --> 06:34.120
I haven't told him yet.

06:34.120 --> 06:35.680
I'm the first?

06:35.680 --> 06:36.880
We're partners.

06:36.880 --> 06:39.080
We're building something together.
(LAUGHS)

06:41.520 --> 06:43.080
What?

06:43.080 --> 06:45.360
You're officially
part of the family.

06:45.360 --> 06:46.360
For now.

06:46.360 --> 06:48.760
Oh, no, admit it -
we've gotten under your skin.

06:48.760 --> 06:50.880
We have weaselled our way
into your heart.

06:50.880 --> 06:52.520
No. I just like the view, OK?

06:52.520 --> 06:55.360
Nah, you're gonna start surfing,
you'll lose the accent.

06:55.360 --> 06:57.720
You're gonna be a real local now.

06:57.720 --> 07:01.920
Well, whatever happens,
you will never see me in corduroy.

07:01.920 --> 07:04.360
Oh, but I look so good.
(LAUGHS)

07:07.920 --> 07:11.160
I heard you stole
all of Snapper's rubber.

07:11.160 --> 07:12.600
Didn't steal it.

07:13.600 --> 07:14.680
Bought it.

07:14.680 --> 07:16.520
Moneybags, eh?

07:16.520 --> 07:18.480
Can I borrow this, Reggie?

07:18.480 --> 07:20.000
What's wrong with your board?

07:24.400 --> 07:26.280
Nice chatting with you too, mate.

07:56.600 --> 07:59.720
MAN: (ON RADIO) It's 6:11.
11 minutes after 6am.

07:59.720 --> 08:02.720
Today, tonight and tomorrow
will be hazy and hot and humid,

08:02.720 --> 08:04.320
with a high today of...

08:45.440 --> 08:46.880
Hey, babe.

08:48.280 --> 08:49.960
Bud, we need to talk.

08:54.280 --> 08:55.560
Everything OK?

08:57.040 --> 08:58.320
It's just that...

08:59.400 --> 09:01.440
..I'm starting
to get some really good roles.

09:01.440 --> 09:04.920
And my agent has some really
important people for me to meet.

09:06.360 --> 09:08.680
And things are just starting
to take off for you.

09:10.320 --> 09:11.520
This is all good.

09:14.840 --> 09:16.000
And now I'm getting fat.

09:16.000 --> 09:17.640
Fat?

09:17.640 --> 09:19.000
What?

09:19.000 --> 09:20.400
No, you're not.

09:21.880 --> 09:23.640
I will though, Bud.

09:26.840 --> 09:31.840
I went to the doctor
and...I'm having a baby.

09:37.760 --> 09:39.400
(LAUGHS)

09:39.400 --> 09:41.640
Hey, this is amazing!

09:41.640 --> 09:42.640
Wha...

09:43.720 --> 09:44.960
Really?

09:44.960 --> 09:46.320
You want it?

09:46.320 --> 09:47.840
Your baby?

09:47.840 --> 09:49.320
Are you...you kidding?

09:49.320 --> 09:50.640
(LAUGHS)

09:50.640 --> 09:51.840
Our baby.

09:53.080 --> 09:54.480
This is just what we need.

09:54.480 --> 09:55.880
I'm in.

09:55.880 --> 09:56.880
You're in?

09:56.880 --> 09:59.000
I'm in. Of course. I'm in.

10:02.160 --> 10:04.040
He knows! (LAUGHS)

10:06.080 --> 10:07.320
Yeah!

10:07.320 --> 10:09.800
Well, I'm not sure
who's gonna father who here,

10:09.800 --> 10:12.120
but I can guarantee

10:12.120 --> 10:16.160
this is going to be the best dressed
baby in all of California.

10:16.160 --> 10:19.120
I'm so excited for you guys.
Thank you.

10:20.160 --> 10:21.760
I'm proud of you.

10:22.920 --> 10:26.000
Hey, why don't you girls go,
ah, whip us up some champagne?

10:26.000 --> 10:28.240
(CONTINUE CHATTING INDISTINCTLY)

10:30.480 --> 10:31.760
(CHAMPAGNE CORK POPS)

10:37.840 --> 10:39.400
Aah!

10:40.520 --> 10:42.000
Did you get the cash?

10:45.040 --> 10:46.560
It's coming.

10:48.320 --> 10:51.760
Man, I cannot wait
to get Trotter off our backs,

10:51.760 --> 10:53.960
just be free to do our own thing,
you know?

10:53.960 --> 10:55.360
Yeah.

10:57.600 --> 10:58.600
Hey.

10:59.640 --> 11:02.040
This is good news, right?

11:02.040 --> 11:03.760
The best.

11:09.240 --> 11:10.760
Champagne.

11:10.760 --> 11:12.080
Neat.

11:15.760 --> 11:18.120
You have to let me
give you a baby shower...

11:20.680 --> 11:22.400
Oh, come on, let her do it...

12:13.640 --> 12:15.240
Where is he now?

12:16.480 --> 12:17.560
I don't care.

12:18.720 --> 12:20.600
Can't believe
you're being so calm about this.

12:20.600 --> 12:23.360
I feel like this huge weight's
been lifted from my shoulders,

12:23.360 --> 12:24.360
to be honest.

12:25.600 --> 12:27.240
I always knew there was
something between them,

12:27.240 --> 12:29.760
but I was always made to feel
like an idiot for even thinking it.

12:34.760 --> 12:36.040
It's Friday night.

12:37.320 --> 12:39.720
Let's go to Snap's place.

12:39.720 --> 12:42.240
I don't think that's a good idea.

12:42.240 --> 12:44.880
You're always going to his parties
and I'm never allowed to go.

12:44.880 --> 12:46.400
Because he's your enemy.

12:50.040 --> 12:51.680
He's Trot's enemy.

12:58.680 --> 13:01.000
(GROANS)
Yes! (GIGGLES)

13:02.080 --> 13:04.520
(LIVELY CHATTER)

13:09.520 --> 13:11.400
I wanna introduce you to somebody.
Come.

13:11.400 --> 13:13.160
Apparently, he's loaded.

13:13.160 --> 13:14.640
He can invest in my film?

13:14.640 --> 13:16.960
Maybe let him invest
in Snapper's comp first.

13:16.960 --> 13:18.880
We don't all have an inheritance.

13:18.880 --> 13:20.360
You guys want more drinks?

13:20.360 --> 13:25.320
Jeez, I would love
a business like this.

13:25.320 --> 13:28.520
Honestly, mate,
I am constantly chasing cashflow.

13:28.520 --> 13:32.320
I mean, turnover's good,
don't get me wrong, but, ah,

13:32.320 --> 13:34.680
I just never actually
feel like I have any money.

13:34.680 --> 13:36.040
(LAUGHS)

13:36.040 --> 13:37.680
Maybe I could help with that, huh?

13:37.680 --> 13:39.600
I mean, you don't have to give me
an answer right now,

13:39.600 --> 13:41.840
but while I'm here I do want to talk
to you about a bigger investment

13:41.840 --> 13:43.240
than just a sponsorship.

13:43.240 --> 13:44.240
Like what?

13:44.240 --> 13:45.240
Like what?

13:45.240 --> 13:46.960
How about like giving you
some proper capital

13:46.960 --> 13:49.120
so you can run your business the way
you want and not have to worry?

13:50.840 --> 13:52.720
You want to wait
until you see the price, right?

13:52.720 --> 13:53.840
Fair enough.

13:53.840 --> 13:55.560
Shall we start
with this announcement?

13:56.760 --> 13:58.480
The Foreman...
Oh, yeah.

13:58.480 --> 14:00.080
Yeah? Yeah?
That's right. Yeah.

14:00.080 --> 14:01.360
OK.
OK.

14:02.600 --> 14:05.880
Um, hey. Alright, everybody!

14:05.880 --> 14:07.280
Gather round.

14:07.280 --> 14:08.520
Minute of your time.

14:08.520 --> 14:11.760
Ah, this is just a quick word

14:11.760 --> 14:14.480
to announce
that Foreman Sporting Goods

14:14.480 --> 14:20.880
is now the official sponsor
of next year's Bare Feet Classic!

14:20.880 --> 14:22.240
(CHEERING)

14:22.240 --> 14:24.680
You can see the prize money
right there.

14:24.680 --> 14:27.800
And, ladies and gentlemen,
the man himself,

14:27.800 --> 14:31.800
Mr Arthur Dodger Foreman!

14:31.800 --> 14:33.480
(CHEERING)
Come on, let's hear it for him.

14:33.480 --> 14:34.560
Hey, ladies, he's single.

14:34.560 --> 14:35.560
I'm not single.

14:35.560 --> 14:37.240
Well, you say that now.

14:37.240 --> 14:40.120
I, for one, am bloody thrilled

14:40.120 --> 14:45.360
that next year we will be able
to offer some real prize money.

14:45.360 --> 14:47.200
The times are finally changing,
folks.

14:47.200 --> 14:48.840
You got a woman's comp yet, Snap?

14:48.840 --> 14:51.600
You get me a cheque, Dani,
and I will get you a competition.

14:51.600 --> 14:56.160
Now, everyone, make sure you show
Dodger Foreman here a good time

14:56.160 --> 14:57.840
as you are getting pissed today,

14:57.840 --> 15:01.600
because he is paying for everything!

15:01.600 --> 15:03.440
(CHEERING)

15:03.440 --> 15:05.400
Bear, come take care of this man.
Yeah.

15:05.400 --> 15:07.080
Have a good time.
Enjoy.

15:10.760 --> 15:14.480
Hey, Dim, how come
you never grew your hair out?

15:14.480 --> 15:16.120
Why do you care?

15:16.120 --> 15:17.480
Honestly, I don't.

15:17.480 --> 15:19.640
Just bored with working here
every night

15:19.640 --> 15:21.360
and not getting anything
back from you.

15:21.360 --> 15:23.120
I talk.

15:23.120 --> 15:25.080
No, mate, you mope.

15:25.080 --> 15:26.560
You mop and you mope.

15:28.640 --> 15:30.200
Maybe I've got a lot on my mind.

15:30.200 --> 15:33.080
You don't think
I've got a few problems, Dim?

15:35.760 --> 15:36.760
Finally.

15:39.160 --> 15:40.400
Breakthrough.

15:46.240 --> 15:48.200
No bloody way.

15:49.920 --> 15:51.560
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa. Easy.

15:51.560 --> 15:53.400
What's this?

15:53.400 --> 15:56.160
I just wanna make sure
you don't burst into flames

15:56.160 --> 15:57.800
as you cross the threshold.

15:57.800 --> 15:59.160
(LAUGHS)

15:59.160 --> 16:00.840
Easy.
I'm OK.

16:02.000 --> 16:03.240
Oh, look at that, you're fine.

16:04.240 --> 16:06.520
I am so not fine, Snap.

16:12.640 --> 16:16.520
(BOTH CHATTER INDISTINCTLY)

16:21.120 --> 16:22.880
Hi, Margaux.

16:22.880 --> 16:24.520
Hi.

16:24.520 --> 16:26.840
Nice trip to Sydney?

16:26.840 --> 16:30.280
Ah, it was a work trip,
so it was quite productive.

16:30.280 --> 16:31.640
Hmm.

16:31.640 --> 16:36.200
Is that how you'd also describe
spending the night with my husband?

16:39.160 --> 16:40.520
Oh.

16:41.840 --> 16:43.040
Tracy, I'm...

16:45.080 --> 16:46.240
How long?

16:47.800 --> 16:50.280
How long has it been going on, huh?

16:50.280 --> 16:51.680
Months?

16:51.680 --> 16:52.960
Or years?

16:54.000 --> 16:55.320
It's not what you think.

16:56.640 --> 16:58.240
I saw you.

16:58.240 --> 16:59.360
I know what it was.

16:59.360 --> 17:00.560
Margaux.

17:02.360 --> 17:03.760
Is this true?

17:07.800 --> 17:09.880
It was just one night.

17:15.880 --> 17:17.120
Run, Sharpie.

17:17.120 --> 17:18.200
Don't look back.

17:18.200 --> 17:19.240
Tracy, I'm sorry.

17:19.240 --> 17:21.080
Apology not accepted.

17:31.840 --> 17:33.320
What are you looking at?

17:34.760 --> 17:36.240
Like you didn't already know!

17:36.240 --> 17:37.800
Trace.

17:37.800 --> 17:40.000
You all knew what happened in Bali

17:40.000 --> 17:42.120
and none of you
cared enough to tell me.

17:42.120 --> 17:45.120
How long have you all been
laughing behind my back, huh?

17:45.120 --> 17:47.040
Keeping Trot's secret safe?

17:47.040 --> 17:48.240
No, we didn't know about this.

17:48.240 --> 17:51.560
Why did you all choose him
and not me?

17:56.440 --> 17:57.800
To be fair...

17:59.640 --> 18:03.160
..you did take my money
and start a rival business with it.

18:03.160 --> 18:06.880
Right where you're standing,
if I recall.

18:24.240 --> 18:26.080
Who has a drink for me?

18:31.640 --> 18:33.560
(GLASS SHATTERS)
Sharpie?

18:33.560 --> 18:35.040
Tom!

18:59.680 --> 19:03.600
(PSYCHEDELIC MUSIC PLAYS)

19:51.240 --> 19:52.520
(MUSIC STOPS)

20:25.000 --> 20:27.360
(LAID-BACK MUSIC PLAYS)

20:53.640 --> 20:54.880
(RETCHES)

20:54.880 --> 20:56.440
Ah, ah, go and do it over there!

20:56.440 --> 20:57.440
(LAUGHS)

20:57.440 --> 20:58.680
(VOMITS)

20:58.680 --> 20:59.840
Oh, God.

20:59.840 --> 21:01.080
Choc, go and take care of him, eh?

21:01.080 --> 21:02.240
Are you serious?

21:03.400 --> 21:05.120
(LAUGHS)

21:06.160 --> 21:07.720
(SIGHS)

21:12.760 --> 21:14.880
I just feel stupid.

21:14.880 --> 21:16.720
Nah.

21:16.720 --> 21:17.960
Don't.

21:17.960 --> 21:18.960
Don't.
I do.

21:18.960 --> 21:20.000
Don't.

21:22.480 --> 21:27.240
I gave him everything and he just
threw it straight back in my face.

21:27.240 --> 21:28.960
Such a nice face.

21:34.000 --> 21:35.240
Honestly?

21:36.880 --> 21:37.880
Yeah.

21:40.280 --> 21:46.320
Did you ever see anyone love anyone
the way that I love Trot?

21:50.520 --> 21:52.080
Not for a long time.

21:53.960 --> 21:55.000
WOMAN: There she is.

21:58.480 --> 21:59.800
(CLEARS THROAT)

22:00.920 --> 22:02.560
(LAUGHS)

22:02.560 --> 22:03.560
Tania!

22:03.560 --> 22:04.640
Dimma!

22:04.640 --> 22:06.160
My lovely brother, ah!

22:06.160 --> 22:07.480
Miss, you're as pissed as a parrot.

22:07.480 --> 22:09.080
I am.

22:09.080 --> 22:10.080
OK.

22:10.080 --> 22:11.480
Hi.
Time to go home.

22:11.480 --> 22:12.600
Oh.

22:12.600 --> 22:13.760
You gonna help?

22:13.760 --> 22:15.000
We just got here.

22:15.000 --> 22:16.240
