42:13.960 --> 42:16.040
I'm joking.

42:16.040 --> 42:18.000
Right.
(LAUGHS)

42:19.360 --> 42:20.600
And Reggie's safe?

42:20.600 --> 42:23.000
Yeah, of course.
He's making me a board to take home.

42:23.000 --> 42:26.600
And no offshore manufacturing, we
keep all the locals on staff, yeah?

42:26.600 --> 42:28.040
Snapper, would you open it up?

42:28.040 --> 42:30.080
I wanna see the look on your face.

42:30.080 --> 42:31.640
Yeah.

42:39.200 --> 42:41.280
And I still get to run
the Bare Feet Classic?

42:42.280 --> 42:44.280
Ah, the Foreman Classic.

42:44.280 --> 42:45.280
What?

42:46.360 --> 42:47.800
Well, you can keep the name
for next year,

42:47.800 --> 42:49.840
you've already got the posters
and everything,

42:49.840 --> 42:52.120
but, ah, look, we're not investing
this much money

42:52.120 --> 42:54.040
to not have our name
on the competition.

42:59.560 --> 43:00.720
No.

43:04.360 --> 43:05.720
Excuse me?

43:10.400 --> 43:11.560
No.

43:16.920 --> 43:18.640
Nah.

43:18.640 --> 43:20.960
No. No way. No.

43:20.960 --> 43:23.680
I listened to you because I thought,

43:23.680 --> 43:26.760
well, here's a man that knows
something about manufacturing,

43:26.760 --> 43:30.520
but you don't know shit
about surf comps.

43:30.520 --> 43:31.600
(LAUGHS AWKWARDLY)

43:31.600 --> 43:34.160
Snapper,
if it's that important to you,

43:34.160 --> 43:36.600
you can still run the surf comp.

43:36.600 --> 43:38.600
Thank you very much, Arthur.

43:39.880 --> 43:41.080
I will.

43:44.880 --> 43:46.360
So you're not selling?

43:46.360 --> 43:49.240
You seem like a decent guy,
but, ah...

43:49.240 --> 43:51.200
And no offence,

43:51.200 --> 43:54.840
you're just not that salty, hmm?

43:54.840 --> 44:00.040
I mean, let's face it, if you ran
this company, you'd just fuck it up.

44:00.040 --> 44:01.240
(LAUGHS)

44:18.480 --> 44:20.200
(CAR DOOR OPENS)

44:21.840 --> 44:24.280
(CAR DOOR CLOSES, ENGINE STARTS)

44:55.840 --> 44:58.240
I heard you were brawling
down at the club.

44:58.240 --> 44:59.720
Hey.

44:59.720 --> 45:01.400
Reggie!

45:01.400 --> 45:03.080
Hey, you want a beer?

45:03.080 --> 45:04.720
Looks like you've had enough
for two.

45:06.440 --> 45:08.400
Come on, have a drink.

45:08.400 --> 45:09.760
Go on, sit down.

45:12.520 --> 45:13.520
(SIGHS)

45:18.640 --> 45:20.840
If you're not gonna drink,
you can piss off, then.

45:21.960 --> 45:24.880
I really thought
you and Tracy were solid, Trot.

45:34.680 --> 45:36.200
So why, then?

45:38.000 --> 45:40.320
I don't know, Reggie.
Why do we do anything?

45:40.320 --> 45:43.120
Nah, I think she's looking
for a better reason than that, Trot.

45:50.160 --> 45:52.040
I am sorry about your beer.

45:53.120 --> 45:54.480
There's still a sip.

46:02.840 --> 46:07.320
You know, when I was a kid, man,
we moved all the time.

46:11.560 --> 46:16.320
But coming here, finding Tracy, I...

46:18.560 --> 46:19.880
It was...

46:23.240 --> 46:24.720
The way she loved me.

46:28.440 --> 46:30.720
I finally felt like I was home.

46:40.840 --> 46:42.920
But there's something in me, Reg...

46:44.680 --> 46:47.040
..as soon as I get my feet
on solid ground,

46:47.040 --> 46:49.080
I start looking at the horizon.

46:50.600 --> 46:53.480
No, mate, that's why you catch
all the best waves.

46:53.480 --> 46:56.080
(LAUGHS) It's why everything I touch
turns to shit.

47:02.600 --> 47:06.240
Buddy met up with Mac in Bali.

47:07.360 --> 47:08.880
Bali run?

47:08.880 --> 47:09.880
Oh.

47:11.040 --> 47:12.040
Shit.

47:15.240 --> 47:18.800
That's how they're getting the money
for the US licence.

47:20.720 --> 47:22.320
Still, it's not like you did it.

47:22.320 --> 47:24.200
Yeah, but I pushed them, you know?

47:25.520 --> 47:27.600
And I knew Buddy was a loose unit.

47:28.760 --> 47:33.360
To pay for a house that leaks,
for a wife who never wanted it,

47:33.360 --> 47:37.120
and don't even get me started
how much I paid for that rubber,

47:37.120 --> 47:38.120
to beat Snapper.

47:38.120 --> 47:41.120
So you're not Mr Clean anymore,
Trotter. Who cares?

47:41.120 --> 47:42.760
And who is?

47:42.760 --> 47:45.160
Yeah, well, that's the thing,
Reggie.

47:46.720 --> 47:48.240
There is more.

47:48.240 --> 47:49.560
I just...

47:51.600 --> 47:54.320
..can't tell you the whole story

47:54.320 --> 47:58.000
because then it's in your head,

47:58.000 --> 48:00.840
and I already
can't get it out of mine.

48:08.200 --> 48:09.520
Here.

48:31.480 --> 48:33.920
You know I actually hate that photo?

48:40.280 --> 48:44.200
It was like everything was good
before you all went on that trip.

48:47.840 --> 48:51.240
Yeah, I was just thinking
that same thing.

48:56.600 --> 48:58.840
Why didn't you tell me
what happened in Bali?

49:05.920 --> 49:07.400
I wanted to.

49:08.720 --> 49:10.840
But you looked so happy.

49:18.400 --> 49:21.120
Guess I thought
you deserved each other.

49:26.160 --> 49:28.240
Heard you're not selling.

49:29.320 --> 49:30.760
This town.

49:30.760 --> 49:33.040
(LAUGHS)

49:35.200 --> 49:37.120
You know,
I could've been a very rich man.

49:37.120 --> 49:38.240
You still might be.

49:38.240 --> 49:40.440
Nah, I don't think I care.

49:42.760 --> 49:44.560
When I started Bare Feet...

49:45.720 --> 49:48.280
..all I wanted
was to make enough money

49:48.280 --> 49:50.440
to live out here

49:50.440 --> 49:53.440
and surf with my mates every day.

49:55.120 --> 49:57.280
You know how often
I get out there now?

49:59.160 --> 50:01.280
I'm guessing as much as I do my art?

50:01.280 --> 50:03.240
Yeah.

50:07.440 --> 50:12.000
They finally offered me enough money
to do what I've always wanted,

50:12.000 --> 50:15.320
and I still said...no.

50:16.600 --> 50:18.600
What does that say about me?

50:41.560 --> 50:43.840
God, I've missed those lips.

50:43.840 --> 50:45.880
I didn't miss that mo.

50:45.880 --> 50:47.120
I'll shave it off.

50:48.200 --> 50:49.480
Really?

50:49.480 --> 50:51.240
Definitely not.

50:51.240 --> 50:52.480
No way.

50:52.480 --> 50:54.480
(LAUGHS)

51:08.680 --> 51:11.080
You really don't know
how to take a hint, do you?

51:11.080 --> 51:12.760
No.

51:12.760 --> 51:14.120
Not with you.

51:34.240 --> 51:36.160
What happened in Bali?

51:43.040 --> 51:44.320
(WEEPS)

51:44.320 --> 51:45.680
Hey...

51:45.680 --> 51:47.480
I've got all night.

55:05.560 --> 55:07.280
Tracy wants to sell LightWave.

55:07.280 --> 55:09.000
There's money about.

55:09.000 --> 55:10.400
It changes people.

55:10.400 --> 55:11.720
You're not selling my company.

55:11.720 --> 55:14.440
It's ours, and I'll do
what I like with my share.

55:14.440 --> 55:15.640
Well, I'm not letting this happen.

55:15.640 --> 55:18.760
No matter how hard you try
to slum it with us,

55:18.760 --> 55:20.840
you're always...
you're gonna be Newport.

55:20.840 --> 55:25.000
Family are the only people that you
should ever go into business with.

55:26.240 --> 55:27.560
So is it true?

55:29.040 --> 55:31.640
A thousand ways
to kneel and kiss the ground,

55:31.640 --> 55:34.160
a thousand ways to go home again.

55:34.160 --> 55:35.560
(LAUGHS)

